text.tspan: Death rates from different causes in France over the 20th century

Reported annual death rate, based on the
underlying cause
listed on death certificates . This is shown as a crude
rate per 100,000 people so it does not account for changes in the age structure of the population.
Data source: Institut National d'Études Démographiques
Note: Causes of death were classified according to the ICD-9 manual . Only a selection of categories are shown.
